- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the issue of lack of proper training and understanding of the computational model in spreadsheet development, which is a human-computer interaction problem. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper discusses computational issues in spreadsheet systems. 
- cs.ED (Education) is relevant as the paper presents a didactical model for teaching spreadsheet development. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the computational model underlying spreadsheet computations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper addresses the problem of high error rates in spreadsheet development, which is a software engineering problem.
